A man was arrested on Wednesday for defiling a nine-month-old girl in Maralal, Samburu county.He had been left with the baby by her grandmother when the incident occurred. The baby was rushed Samburu County Referral Hospital for treatment.Area OCPD Abaggarro Guyo said the suspect is currently detained at Maralal police station."We have detained the suspect for interrogation and further investigations as doctors examine the baby," he said.Duke Mogaka, a doctor at the hospital, said the baby has severe injuries on her private parts and was bleeding heavily."We have assessed and recommended reconstructive surgery to restore torn muscles," he said.Mogaka also advised residents against leaving their children under the care of suspicious people.